                "name": "Priyanka Kashyap",
                "href": "/profile/Priyanka-Kashyap-40"
            },
            "answer_text": "Here is a list of things that will surely guide you through the revision \u2013 Make short notes - If you develop the habit of writing and jotting down a few key concepts from every topic that you study and read, it will help you tremendously to revise GATE subjects. Short notes can be read later when your memory of the concept is getting blurred.Carefully make revision points - While reading a topic, you should carefully determine important points of that concept. The best way to do so is to first focus on understanding the relevant topic. Once your concepts are clear, then you should make a summary of the same by jotting down all the important key points/ steps that would enable your understanding of the same topic again.Revision notes may contain important terminology, definitions, formulas, examples - It is important that you include important terminology, definitions, formulas, examples etc. in your revision notes, otherwise they not come in as handy during your revision time. Think of your revision notes as your own small guide to the syllabus.Revision notes should be precise - While your revision notes should be extensive, you also need to make sure that they are as small as possible. There is no need to add everything. Only include details of the concept which are absolutely essential in ensuring your understanding of it.Prepare revision notes regularly - You should prepare revision notes at least 3 to 4 times in a month or once in a week. This would ensure that you are not burdened with the note-making task for the last moment.Hope this helps!!! ",
