                "href": "/profile/Saghan-Agrawal"
            },
            "answer_text": "Revision is the key to excel in any competetive exam which includes a huge syllabus.You can follow the following points to have a good revision:- Make short notes after finishing the subject. These short notes must be about 20\u201330 pages per subject and should include all the formulaes, important concepts, tricky questions.Revise these short notes once a week per subject as there are 10 subjects in total therefore you will be revising 10 subjects for about 10 times in 10 weeks. Revision of a subject should take approx 30\u201345 minutes.In the month of December, make separate notes for revision which must be shorter than previous ones(5\u20137 pages) and follow the same schedule of revision.Whenever u feel that you are not confident about a particular subject , study thay subject from your short notes of 20\u201330 pages.The more a subject will come in front of your eyes, the more your mind will capture. ",
